<C>__{warm springs}
<D>__{written by margaret nagle shooting draft: 9.14.2004}
<T>__{fade in:}
<L>__{exterior a body of water late afternoon}
<A>__{a glimpse of sunlight desperately tries to force its way through a gray sky before being obliterated. a man, sunburned and bearded, lets himself fall from the edge of a boat and into the ocean. underwater, through shafts of light, white limbs are flailing. the man struggles, alone. bubbles stream upward. he breaks the surface and gasps for air. he begins to swim. his massive arms and shoulders grab at the tide in large, hard strokes. his legs and feet are buried beneath the dark ocean water.}
